§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the empty set by $∅$. ⦉

  ‖ In other words, in all future accounts (see␣
    <a href='/sheets/accounts.html'>
      ‖ Accounts ⦉
    </a>
    ), there are two implicit lines. First, “⁅name⁆ $∅$” and
    second “⁅have⁆ $(∀ x)(x ∉ ∅)$”. ⦉
⦉

§ Properties ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ It is immediate from our definition of the empty set and
    of the definition of inclusion (see␣
    <a href='/sheets/set_inclusion.html'>
      ‖ Set Inclusion ⦉
    </a>
    ) that the empty set is included in every set (including
    itself). ⦉
⦉

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $(∀ A)(∅ ⊂ A)$ ⦉
</statement>
<proof>
  ‖ Suppose toward contradiction that $∅ \not⊂ A$. ⦉

  ‖ Then there exists $y ∈ ∅$ such that $y \not ∈ A$. ⦉

  ‖ But this is impossible, since $(∀ x)(x \not ∈ ∅)$. ⦉
</proof>
